wiki.summary: "Barbie World" is American rappers Ice Spice and Nicki Minaj's take on the “Barbie The Movie“ soundtrack. The song samples the 1997 Barbie iconic anthem "Barbie Girl" by Aqua, and is the second duet between the rappers, after "Princess Diana (Remix)". In the United States, "Barbie World" debuted at number seven on the Billboard Hot 100 with 16.2 million streams, 37,000 digital downloads sold, and 4.7 million airplay audience matching the peak of "Barbie Girl". Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Barbie World" is American rappers Ice Spice and Nicki Minaj's take on the “Barbie The Movie“ soundtrack. The song samples the 1997 Barbie iconic anthem "Barbie Girl" by Aqua, and is the second duet between the rappers, after "Princess Diana (Remix)". In the United States, "Barbie World" debuted at number seven on the Billboard Hot 100 with 16.2 million streams, 37,000 digital downloads sold, and 4.7 million airplay audience matching the peak of "Barbie Girl". Barbie World also claimed the position of #1 on the Digital Songs Chart and topped The Hot 100. Read more on Last.fm.
